# CV Module Conventions

## Module layout
- `config.py` — all tuneable constants, no logic
- `detector.py` — YOLO wrapper, returns best detection dict or None
- `estimator.py` — direction zones + distance heuristic, pure functions
- `main.py` — camera loop, POST loop, debug display

## Key constraints
- Frame size must stay 640x480 (speed)
- Use `yolov8n.pt` (nano), never medium/large on MacBook
- POST must happen every 100ms regardless of detection result (Pi expects heartbeat)
- POST errors must print a warning and NOT crash the loop (try/except around every POST)
- Camera source is set in config.CAMERA_SOURCE — never hardcode it

## Detection dict shape
```python
{"label": str, "confidence": float, "cx": int, "cy": int,
 "box_h": int, "x1": int, "y1": int, "x2": int, "y2": int}
```

## Payload shape (always send this exact structure)
```python
{"obstacle": bool, "direction": str, "distance_m": float|None, "confidence": float}
```

## Distance calibration
Hold object at 1.0m, press 'c' in the debug window to capture reference height.
Formula: `distance_m = (REFERENCE_HEIGHT_PX * 1.0) / box_h`
